begin_memory_text: We talked about where we each live and the work each of us do. We talked about how online schooling must be really challenging right now, and how it is hard to stay connected to friends when you cant see them in person.
middle_memory_text: We talked about movies and podcasts we like, and how we have a hard time sitting still and not doing anything while we watch a movie. She showed me her adult coloring book that is her new hobby, and I talked about my knitting project. We also talked a bit about how I changed my wedding plans.
end_memory_text: We talked about why I moved my wedding date up and my first date with my husband. We both like the idea of not living with a partner before marriage, and I talked about why that was important to me. She talked about the struggles of online dating and how she isn't sure that she'd want to do a video date right now.
rest_of_day_open: later this week I will continue to go in to work, and then on Friday I will have a group lunch with my coworkers. We will then take the afternoon off to celebrate finishing potato harvest. Then my friend will come over on Friday night and we will play board games and eat tacos. I will try to catch up on some house chores on Saturday.
critical_positive: She was upbeat and friendly, and was good at holding a conversation. My partner seemed interested in getting to know me, and I also asked good questions to engage her. She shared openly about how things are going, and was willing to respond to what I was saying. I was glad to talk to someone because I was doing homework before this, so it was nice to just chit chat for a while. She smiled a lot and used encouraging facial expressions.
critical_negative: We had maybe two or three pauses in the conversation, which was not terrible, just some normal "strangers talking to each other" type pauses. I wanted to ask more about her job, but by the time I had formed a question I felt like we had moved on to other topics. I felt a bit bad because she was asking me good questions about my work but I did not reciprocate.

begin_memory_text: We talked about our jobs and how she just got married during covid.  Her husband was putting up pictures from their wedding.   She is a potato specialist and works on potatoes and processing for potatoes, working with Frito Lay and others.
middle_memory_text: We talked about movies and hobbies.  She showed me her knitting that she has picked up during quarantine and we talked about podcasts.  We both have listened to the Office Ladies podcast.
end_memory_text: We talked about travel and dating.  I mentioned putting dating on hold although Bumble has video date options.  I gave her kudos on waiting to live with her husband until they got married...she said that they moved the wedding up so she sold her house and moved in with him married.
rest_of_day_open: I think my week will go well.  It is Wednesday so it is hump day and I feel ready to go hit a workout after having a nice chat.  It was refreshing to hear that her husband respected her decision to not live together before being married and that is rare these days.
critical_positive: I think we both have similar educational backgrounds (master's degrees) and own houses, we work hard.  I think we both tried to find commonalities and to relate to one another by talking about tv shows, movies, podcasts, travel and lifestyle (married vs. single /dating).  I think we each showed respect and interest
critical_negative: At times we both seemed unsure about what next to talk about, and how to keep the conversation flowing.  I felt like we both may have been a little tired, and we had paused to think about a question or two to ask the other to keep the conversation going.
